                                    <div class="margin-bottom-5">
        <h3>Semantic Model of Internal Controls in Database Design</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="margin-bottom-10">
            <a href="/contributors/451">De, Prabuddha</a> and     <a href="/contributors/453">Sen, Arun</a>    </div>

<p>ABSTRACT: The paper attempts to model internal controls in an organization from a database perspective. It provides a three-level architecture to integrate data, process, and control level abstractions. A semantic formalism based on this architecture is presented.</p>

    <strong>Key words and phrases: </strong>
        <a href="/keywords/288">internal controls</a>,    <a href="/keywords/289">data models</a>,    <a href="/keywords/290">constraint specification</a>
                                
                        
